The paper proposes a new concept called "info intervention" in causal modeling, which is relevant to several sub-fields in computer science. Specifically, it involves information processing and manipulation, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). It also involves the identification of cause-effect relationships, which is relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper proposes a new framework for causal modeling, which is related to systems and control theory (cs.SI).
